          "Created By:"
        ],
        [
          "A Vain, Scheming Tremere, who weaponizes underestimation to achieve their goals, and cannot handle any tarnishment to their beauty.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Logan Boese"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Most things came Easy to them as they grew, they were always as bright as they were beautiful. But, as time went on, and their beauty became more pronounced, they saw that they were judged first and foremost by that, and realized that they gained little to nothing to dissuade people of those initial impressions, but much by letting them think that they were little more than a brainless beauty. They developed an intense interest in old stories of magic, and dove headlong into finding sources of true occult ability. Like most things, they found that they possessed a natural affinity for the powers of the hedge magicians, and practiced it with ease, delighting in any chance they got to show off their abilities. Gradually, however, as they discovered that there was a deeper, more complex and powerful form of Mystical Ability, they grew tired of their \"Parlour Tricks,\" And strove instead to master True Magick. However, they found they hadn't the same easy time with that, and rather than devote their lives to study, they instead opted to try to find a teacher to streamline the Process. Their search didn't last long, as a Former Hermeticist did appear to them very shortly, attracted by their wanton displays and flaunting of their minor hedge magicks, initially intending to end them to preserve the secrecy of all magicks, but after discussing things with them, they saw the use of such an Apt Pupil, and instead decided to give them the Magickal power they craved, if not in the form they'd initially expected. They were embraced into clan Tremere, and found that little had changed for them. Most things still came easy to them, and they still excelled. Their Beauty was even still weaponized, though in a slightly different way. Their clan could use their face to further their own ends, to gather information. And that, alone made them Useful, and gained them favour. It was simple, Stand in a corner and be beautiful. Act as if there was no brain in behind those pretty eyes. Watch. Listen. Learn. And capitalize. And They watched, and listened, and have time and again used that underestimation to capitalize on their opponent's weaknesses, and turn the tables to the favour of themselves and Clan Tremere. They know that their face is one of their greatest weapons, and they will keep it pristine for utility. (At least, that's what they tell themselves.) Early in their apprenticeship, their inquiries lead to them being offered a deal by something that purported to be a demon. but They were well acquainted with stories of how such dealings ended, and they refused. Enraged at the rejection, the demon cursed them, that \"Their heart would be forever chilled to others around them, to never know the warmth of true affection to another.\" Given that, if they had ever valued such things, they would have had to fall to the wayside now anyway, and the Demon hadn't touched their face, they took it as a blessing."
        ],
        [
