rain in behind those pretty eyes. Watch. Listen. Learn. And capitalize. And They watched, and listened, and have time and again used that underestimation to capitalize on their opponent's weaknesses, and turn the tables to the favour of themselves and Clan Tremere. They know that their face is one of their greatest weapons, and they will keep it pristine for utility. (At least, that's what they tell themselves.) Early in their apprenticeship, their inquiries lead to them being offered a deal by something that purported to be a demon. but They were well acquainted with stories of how such dealings ended, and they refused. Enraged at the rejection, the demon cursed them, that \"Their heart would be forever chilled to others around them, to never know the warmth of true affection to another.\" Given that, if they had ever valued such things, they would have had to fall to the wayside now anyway, and the Demon hadn't touched their face, they took it as a blessing."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Sire:",
          "column_2": "Marie Penstemmon",
          "column_3": "Reference: (If any)",
          "column_6": "Clan",
          "column_7": "Tremere - Easily Bound"
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Embrace Date:",
          "column_2": "1905-06-05 00:00:00",
          "column_3": "Embrace Location:",
          "column_4": "Cardiff, Wales",
          "column_6": "Generation",
          "column_7": "Ancilla 9"
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Who You Know",
          "column_2": "Your relationship to these people is described. This may mean they do not know you."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Starting Goals",
          "column_2": "These are recomendations, not mandates."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Protect your face. It's been your greatest weapon time and time again. Use it, but care for it, and make certain NOTHING happens to it."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "You've taken the typical path of Thaumaturgy nearly as far as you can. Perhaps  you should look into Mastery of the Elements? Seems both Flashy and Useful."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Play up your brainlessness. Your lightheartedness. Your ditziness and your Cowardice, Then Capitalize and Punish those who fall for it"
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Regency. Plain and Simple. It will be yours."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Player Amended History",
          "column_3": "Date Submited"
        }
      ]
